```
This `update_policy` ensures that only the author of the blog post, identified by the current user's ID, can update the post.

Of course! Here's an example of how you might define an access policy in SDL for a `Movie` type. This policy allows any authenticated user to read movies, but only allows users with the 'admin' role to update or delete them.

```sdl
type Movie {
  required title: str;
  multi actors: Person;

  access policy allow_all_read {
    using (true);
    allow read;
  }

  access policy restrict_write_to_admins {
    using (SELECT 'admin' = sys::get_current_role_name());
    allow update, delete;
  }
}
```

In this example, `allow_all_read` is an access policy that allows read access to all authenticated users, and `restrict_write_to_admins` only allows update and delete operations if the current user has the 'admin' role. Remember that the actual resolution of these policies will follow the algorithm EdgeDB uses when multiple policies are present.

